               <head>Historical anecdotes, Persian and Arabic</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Khulāṣat al-ḥikāyāt by Fayz̤ Allāh ibn Zayn al-ʿĀbidīn Banbānī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115302 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104967 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064938" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3730-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7124">Fayz̤ Allāh ibn Zayn al-ʿĀbidīn Banbānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7124">فيض الله ابن زين العابدين بنبانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21826">Khulāṣat al-ḥikāyāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21826">خلاصة الحكايات</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of anecdotes concerning people and incidents based on early Arabic and Persian historical and biographical sources, compiled by Fayz̤ Allāh ibn Zayn al-ʿĀbidīn Banbānī, entitled Ṣadr Jahān, dedicated to the sultan of Gujarat, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_306386706" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/no2014018082" role="pat">Sulṭān Abū al-Fatḥ Maḥmūd Shāh ibn Muḥammad Shāh</persName> (r. <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">867-917</date>/<date calendar="Gregorian">1459-1511</date>)
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into 21 chapters</p>
                        <p>Ruled after f. 12</p>
                        <p>Copied in multiple hands (<term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">taʿlīq</term>)
                        </p>
                        <p>Rare</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
